# Data conventions

## Explore / beaches

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `countries.json` | Country list + `city_zones[]` with ids |
| `{country}/country.json` | Ocean overview, coast guide |
| `{country}/search-index.json` | Country trie source: names, aliases, `search_tags` |
| `{city_zone}/city-beaches.json` | Beach index: `{ id, name, tags, path }` |
| `{beach}/beach.json` | Full record: `live_rating`, `live_rating.tide.{next_high,next_low}`, `ecosystem`, `map_link` |

Use kebab-case slugs for ids. `live_rating` scores are 0–10 integers where numeric.

## Education / marine life

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `marine-life/index.json` | Category registry |
| `animals/index.json` / `plants/index.json` | Card index with `path` |
| `{slug}.json` | Species card for UI pages |

Cross-ref beaches → species via slug only (no embedded duplicates).

## Eco Shop

`data/eco_shop/{category}/catalog.json` — product evaluations 0–10.

Do not hardcode product or beach counts — read the index JSON.
